Diagnosis.
Dorsal shield with 33 pairs of setae, 11 pairs of marginal (
r -R
) and six pairs of sub-marginal (
UR
) on the lateral unsclerotised cuticle. Ventrianal shield vase-shaped, reticulated anteriorly and laterally around anal opening, bearing three pairs of opisthogastric setae (
JV1–JV3
). Sternal shield nearly smooth, with concave posterior margin; peritreme short 20 (18–21), reaching to the median level of coxa III; fixed cheliceral digit shorter than movable digit, with two teeth in addition to apical tooth, and with a long setiform pilus dentilis. Spermathecal calyx hornlike; atrium globular; minor duct as long as calyx.
